						<summary>

						

						<p><hi rend="bold">King: ⎯⎯ Year: <hi rend="italic">Jaya, Māgha</hi>, śu. 11 Friday.</hi></p>						

						<p>The figures of moon, trident, and sun are depicted at the top.</p>						

						<p>This inscription is in characters of the 16th century A.D. and records the taxfree grant of a village, Chauḍāpura, to the goddess Chauḍēśvaramma of Uṭukūr by the (chief) Nalakōṭi-nāyaka on the advice of Kṛishṇapa-nāyaka, the son of Chinnapanāyaka. It is also recorded that this is called charter of Chauḍāpura. Usual imprecatory portion figures at the end.</p>						

						</summary>
